headline: Snap-on (SNA): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q4 Earnings?
summary: Since March 2020, the S&P 500 has delivered a total return of 113%. But one standout stock has nearly doubled the market - over the past five years, Snap-on has surged 201% to $327.91 per share. Its momentum hasn’t stopped as it’s also gained 13.2% in the last six months, beating the S&P by 17.3%.
